- VSCode Version: code-oss-dev 1.16.0 (9066eedcf7597779e3a710bf997d0d9f8748d597)
- OS Version: Windows_NT x64 10.0.15063
---

I gave `.code-workspace` files another try since they now became suitable for my use-case with support for relative paths (#31203). It works great, as long as I don't add any additional folders to it via the UI and use `Save Workspace As...`. If I do that, VSCode **turns the relative file paths into absolute ones**.

In my particular case, this isn't really an issue, since I auto-generate the file, but it still seems like VSCode should try to preserve the "relativity" of the file paths so `code-workspace` files can be checked into repositories.

---

Steps to reproduce:

1. Open any workspace with relative paths in its `.code-workspace` file (I'm using [this one](https://github.com/HaxeFlixel/flixel-demos/blob/dev/flixel-demos.code-workspace)).
1. Add any other folder to that workspace via `File -> Add Folder to Workspace...` (removing a folder works too).
1. Save the workspace with `File -> Save Workspace As...` in the same location.

As an example, this:

```json
{
	"folders": [
		{
			"path": "Arcade/Breakout"
		}
	]
}
```

will be turned into:

```json
{
	"folders": [
		{
			"path": "c:\\HaxeToolkit\\haxe\\lib\\flixel-demos\\git\\Arcade\\Breakout"
		},
		{
			"path": "c:\\HaxeToolkit\\haxe\\lib\\flixel-demos\\git\\Arcade\\FlxSnake"
		}
	]
}
```

..when adding the `Arcade/FlxSnake` folder.

Note: when saving the workspace _without_ adding or removing any folders, the file remains unchanged, which is good.
